Ford-Kenya has picked Governor Patrick Khaemba to fly the party flag in Trans Nzoia. In a press statement to newsrooms on Thursday, the party&#39;s management committee stated that it had adopted the resolutions of branch and other party officials to have Khaemba picked by consensus to fly the party flag. &quot;Today we have adopted the resolutions of the party&#39;s Trans Nzoia branch that, among others, sought to pick and field the current governor by consensus. The decision is meant to guard the party against a fractious nomination...&quot; read the statement.&nbsp;